1.11	The_Prize_(1963_film)	The Prize (1963 film)	The Prize is a 1963 spy film starring Paul Newman, Elke Sommer and Edward G. Robinson. It was directed by Mark Robson, produced by Pandro S. Berman and adapted for the screen by Ernest Lehman from the novel of the same name by Irving Wallace. It also features an early score by prolific composer Jerry Goldsmith.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/16/The_prize_moviep.jpg/220px-The_prize_moviep.jpg
